# ============================================================
# alicevision-for-mac — .gitignore
# ============================================================
# Single source of truth for the monorepo. The two venv subdirs
# (docs-venv/, meshroom-venv/) carry their own auto-generated
# venv-level .gitignore files (`*`) — those don't conflict;
# they're ignored at the parent level here anyway.
#
# NOTE: gitignore does NOT support inline `#` comments — each
# pattern is on its own line; comments go on separate lines.

# ---------- Build artifacts ----------
build/
build-*/
dist/
# mkdocs build output:
site/
# ctest scratch at repo root:
Testing/
CMakeCache.txt
CMakeFiles/
*.o
*.air
*.metallib
*.dylib
*.dSYM/
compile_commands.json
# Swift Package Manager build cache (meshroom-native/):
.build/
*.xcodeproj/
*.xcworkspace/
.swiftpm/

# ---------- Python virtual envs ----------
docs-venv/
meshroom-venv/
.venv/
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# ---------- Editor / OS / IDE / cache ----------
.DS_Store
.cache/
.claude/
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*~

# ---------- External, NOT tracked in this repo ----------
# `upstream/` is a symlink to the read-only reference AliceVision
# clone outside this monorepo (resolves to
# ../alicevision-windows/AliceVision). Contributors create it
# locally per the build doc.
upstream

# `meshroom-mac/` IS now tracked (S51 monorepo consolidation).
# It's a clean copy of upstream Meshroom (commit 0ab90c0b) with
# Mac patches pre-applied (S42 + S51 Windows-cruft removal:
# `start.bat`, `docs/make.bat` deleted). Patches under
# `patches/meshroom/` + `patches/alicevision-meshroom/` kept as
# the historical record of what we changed FROM upstream stock.
#
# DO NOT add `meshroom-mac/` to ignore list — that breaks the
# monorepo. Use `git rm -r meshroom-mac/` if you ever need to
# regenerate it from upstream.

# Meshroom RUN outputs (generated artefacts; not source).
meshroom-mac-out/
meshroom-out/

# Meshroom-specific build artefacts inside meshroom-mac/ tree
# (Qt/QML compiled forms, IDE projects, install staging).
*.qmlc
*.jsc
*.qmlproject*
*.creator*
*.cflags
*.cxxflags
meshroom-mac/install/
meshroom-mac/build/
meshroom-mac/dist/
meshroom-mac/dl/
meshroom-mac/.tests/
meshroom-mac/.pytest_cache/
meshroom-mac/data/
meshroom-mac/docs/build/
meshroom-mac/docs/source/generated/
.meshroom-venv/

# ---------- Test datasets ----------
# Downloadable from sources documented in `docs/user/pipeline.md`.
# Don't bloat the repo with test imagery; users fetch on demand.
dataset_monstree/
dataset_middlebury/
dataset_*/

# ---------- Vendored deps that download themselves ----------
# metal-cpp (~1 MB) ships fresh from developer.apple.com per the
# build doc. The local copy stays VCS-ignored so we don't pin
# a snapshot.
third_party/metal-cpp/
# LEMON (32 MB) IS tracked — patched per S39; see
# third_party/CMakeLists.txt header for vendoring rationale.

# ---------- Agent / session-state (private to author) ----------
# Session-handover notes for AI-assisted dev:
memory/
# Author's reference PDFs:
books/
# Author-local instructions:
instructions/

# ---------- AI segmentation models ----------
# Large ONNX / CoreML model files downloaded by
# `scripts/download_models.py`. Too big for git (BiRefNet-general
# is ~973 MB). The folder itself is tracked (with README) but
# model files are not.
ai-models/*.onnx
ai-models/*.mlpackage
ai-models/*.mlmodel
ai-models/*.bin
ai-models/.cache/
